  - m_Id: 5813024030932992
    m_Localized: 'The objective of the game is to fill your shelf with all the items;
      the first player to achieve this, wins.





'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5813184354009088
    m_Localized: To obtain the items, you must land on the shop squares and have
      money. Then, you have to answer the question correctly.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5813222723502080
    m_Localized: To obtain the necessary money, you need to land on a question square
      and answer the corresponding question correctly.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5813244378693632
    m_Localized: 'There are two types of money: saved money, represented by the wallet,
      and cash, represented by the bills. Everyone starts with $200 saved.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5813263819292672
    m_Localized: "\rEach player has an inventory in which they can carry up to 6
      items. Once the inventory is full, they cannot buy more items."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5813282307784704
    m_Localized: "\rTo complete the shelf, you must land on your base. At that moment,
      your inventory will be emptied, and you will save your cash."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5813321826516992
    m_Localized: 'The turns are always played in the same order: yellow player, red
      player, green player, and blue player.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5813338217857024
    m_Localized: "\rA player can play on their turn until they fail a question, whether
      it's on a question square, in the shop, or during a duel."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5813363211714560
    m_Localized: 'There are 3 types of squares on the board: question squares, shop
      squares, and base squares.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5813396917141504
    m_Localized: "\rIf a player lands on the question square, they will have to answer
      a question from the corresponding category; if they answer correctly, they
      will earn $50."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5813409089011712
    m_Localized: 'The categories are as follows: blue for geography, orange for sports,
      yellow for history, green for science, purple for art, and pink for entertainment.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5813448674852864
    m_Localized: "\rIf a player lands on a shop square, they can buy an item as long
      as they have $200, combining both cash and saved money. In case they have money
      in both, cash will be spent first."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
      - rid: 3894796172405506048
  - m_Id: 5813463925342208
    m_Localized: "\rIf the player can buy an item, they must decide which item to
      purchase. Then, they have to answer a question of the corresponding category.
      If they answer correctly, they get the item; if they fail, they don't lose
      the money but do lose the turn."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5813478362136576
    m_Localized: "\rIf a player lands on their base square, they will empty their
      inventory and cash."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5813513829171200
    m_Localized: "\rIf a player lands on a question square where one or more players
      are already present, a duel begins. The last player to land will decide which
      player they want to steal from."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5813533198467072
    m_Localized: Once chosen, the player will decide whether they want to steal an
      item or money from that player. If they choose to steal an item, they must
      decide which one. If they choose to steal money, the money at stake will be
      $100.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5813552668426240
    m_Localized: After choosing, they will be asked a question based on the category
      of the square they are on. If they answer correctly, they will steal what they
      asked for. If they fail, they will lose their turn.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
